radiographic_examinations.findings: The appendix is thickened to a maximum diameter of 1.2 cm with wall thickening, periappendiceal stranding, and mild thickening of the adjacent peritoneal wall. The remainder of the abdominal and pelvic organs are unremarkable, with no evidence of obstruction, ascites, pneumoperitoneum, or hernias. No focal lesions in the osseous structures.
